text: Else Marie Fjære (born 2 July 1944) is a Norwegian speed skater and track and athlete. She competed at the 1960 World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women. She won the 1962 Norwegian Championships for Girls. == References == Category:1944 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian speed skaters Category:Norwegian athletes Category:Shot putters Category:Javelin throwers
